name: Notices of the American Mathematical Society
summary: Notices of the American Mathematical Society is the membership journal of the American Mathematical Society (AMS), published monthly except for the combined June/July issue. The first volume was published in 1953. Each issue of the magazine since January 1995 is available in its entirety on the journal web site. Articles are peer-reviewed by an editorial board of mathematical experts. Beginning with the January 2025 issue, the editor-in-chief is Mark C. Wilson, succeeding past editor Erica Flapa
